  "excerpt": "<p>Categorizing your Assets: Tagging and Taxonomy Options Adding and Editing Topics from Settings There are multiple locations within DataTools Pro where you can potentially add and edit your Lines of Business and Topics. 1. In the top right toolbar, click on the Settings gear icon 2. Go to the Settings page in DataTools Pro and [&hellip;]</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-wideright\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\"><div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a class=\"aioseo-toc-item\" href=\"#aioseo-categorizing-your-assets-tagging-and-taxonomy-options\">Categorizing your Assets: Tagging and Taxonomy Options</a></li><li><a class=\"aioseo-toc-item\" href=\"#aioseo-adding-and-editing-topics-from-settings\">Adding and Editing Topics from Settings</a></li><li><a class=\"aioseo-toc-item\" href=\"#aioseo-adding-and-editing-categories-from-metrics-or-dashboard-and-reports-info-windows\">Adding and Editing Categories from Metrics or Dashboard and Reports Info Windows</a></li><li><a class=\"aioseo-toc-item\" href=\"#assignsinglecategory\">Assign Categories to a Single Metric, Report or Dashboard</a></li><li><a class=\"aioseo-toc-item\" href=\"#aioseo-remove-an-assigned-categories-to-a-metric-report-or-dashboard\">Remove an assigned categories to a Metric, Report or Dashboard</a></li><li><a class=\"aioseo-toc-item\" href=\"#bulkassigncategories\">Bulk Assign Categories to a Single Metric, Report or Dashboard</a></li><li><a class=\"aioseo-toc-item\" href=\"#aioseo-permissions-team-and-enterprise-versions\">Permissions (Team and Enterprise Versions)</a></li></ul></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>DataTools Pro free Salesforce app allows you to tag Salesforce Reports and Dashboards by line of business and topic. Semantics and taxonomies are terms that mean you are simply categorizing your assets. When it comes to analytics you want to categorize your metrics, reports, and dashboards in a way describes how you manage your business! That is why we created a feature that allows you to categorize, Reports &amp; Dashboards and Metrics so you can easily filter  and explore. </p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-categorizing-your-assets-tagging-and-taxonomy-options\">Categorizing your Assets: Tagging and Taxonomy Options</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p><strong>Line of Business </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The most common taxonomy for an enterprise that is generally universal is line of business. That is why we have added Line of Business a standard DataTools Pro tag type.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Custom Categories</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Feel free to contact us for more information how to create and use custom tags and taxonomies.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p><strong>Topics</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Topic is a general tag that can vary by organization. Within DataTools Pro, we wanted to provide maximum flexibility for users to define their own topics.</p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Tag Salesforce Reports and Dashboards by Lne of Business and Topic\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZLpZTLZZAHI?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-adding-and-editing-topics-from-settings\">Adding and Editing Topics from Settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are multiple locations within DataTools Pro where you can potentially add and edit your Lines of Business and Topics.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. In the top right toolbar, click on the <strong>Settings </strong>gear icon</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"b2afb6\" data-has-transparency=\"true\" style=\"--dominant-color: #b2afb6;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"265\" height=\"135\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-32-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10374 has-transparency\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>2. Go to the <strong>Settings</strong> page in DataTools Pro and scroll down to the Categories section.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"e8eaed\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #e8eaed;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"784\" height=\"449\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-31-png.webp\" alt=\"Tag Salesforce Reports\" class=\"wp-image-10373 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-31-png.webp 784w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-31-300x172.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-31-768x440.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 784px) 100vw, 784px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"managecategories\" id=\"managetags\">3. <strong>Add and Edit Lines of Business and Topics</strong>:<br>You will find two categories: <strong>Lines of Business</strong> and <strong>Topics</strong>. Use the spreadsheet interface to easily add new tags or edit existing ones.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9f9f9\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9f9f9;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"472\" height=\"285\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-33-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10375 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-33-png.webp 472w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-33-300x181.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 472px) 100vw, 472px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"managetags\"><strong>Examples</strong>:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Lines of Business</strong>: Product, Marketing, Sales, Support.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Topics</strong>: Customer Acquisition, Retention, Funnel Analysis.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-adding-and-editing-categories-from-metrics-or-dashboard-and-reports-info-windows\">Adding and Editing Categories from Metrics or Dashboard and Reports Info Windows</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you view an individual Metric, Report, or Dashboard info-window, you can assign a category and also add new categories for convenience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Select a Metric, Report or Dashboard to display the info-window.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"8d8f8d\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #8d8f8d;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"686\" height=\"336\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-png.webp\" alt=\"Select infowindow\" class=\"wp-image-10377 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-png.webp 686w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-300x147.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 686px) 100vw, 686px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Scroll the Line of Business and Topic section.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Click the edit icon (pencil).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"fcfcfc\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #fcfcfc;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"396\" height=\"191\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10376 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-png.webp 396w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-300x145.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 396px) 100vw, 396px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Go to the &#8220;Not Related&#8221; sub tab to display a list of categories not associated with the Metric, Report or Dashboard</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9fbfb\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9fbfb;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"381\" height=\"245\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-36-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10378 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-36-png.webp 381w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-36-300x193.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 381px) 100vw, 381px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Click the &#8220;Add&#8221; button to 3. <a href=\"#managecategories\" title=\"\"><strong>Add and Edit Lines of Business and Topics</strong>:<br></a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"assignsinglecategory\">Assign Categories to a Single Metric, Report or Dashboard</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you view an individual Metric, Report, or Dashboard info-window, you can assign a category and also add new categories for convenience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Select a Metric, Report or Dashboard to display the info-window.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"8d8f8d\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #8d8f8d;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"686\" height=\"336\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-png.webp\" alt=\"Select infowindow\" class=\"wp-image-10377 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-png.webp 686w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-300x147.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 686px) 100vw, 686px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Scroll the Line of Business and Topic section.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Click the edit icon (pencil).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"fcfcfc\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #fcfcfc;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"396\" height=\"191\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10376 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-png.webp 396w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-300x145.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 396px) 100vw, 396px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>4. By default, if you have not assigned a category (line of business or topic) to the record you selected, you will see &#8220;Not Related&#8221; by default.  If you have a category already assigned, click on the &#8220;Not Related&#8221; sub tab to display a list of categories not associated with the Metric, Report or Dashboard</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9fbfb\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9fbfb;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"381\" height=\"245\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-36-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10378 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-36-png.webp 381w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-36-300x193.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 381px) 100vw, 381px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Click on the Line of Business or Category in the list to relate the category to your metric, report or dashboard. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>NOTE: The &#8220;Add&#8221; button is to create a brand new category and is not used to relate your category.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-remove-an-assigned-categories-to-a-metric-report-or-dashboard\">Remove an assigned categories to a Metric, Report or Dashboard</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To remove a category relationship to a Metric, Report or Dashboard:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Select a Metric, Report or Dashboard to display the infowindow.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"8d8f8d\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #8d8f8d;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"686\" height=\"336\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-png.webp\" alt=\"Select infowindow\" class=\"wp-image-10377 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-png.webp 686w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-35-300x147.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 686px) 100vw, 686px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Scroll the Line of Business and Topic section.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Click the edit icon (pencil).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"fcfcfc\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #fcfcfc;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"396\" height=\"191\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10376 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-png.webp 396w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-34-300x145.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 396px) 100vw, 396px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Click the &#8220;Trash&#8221; icon to move the related category back to &#8220;Not Related&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9fbfb\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9fbfb;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"368\" height=\"183\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-37-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10379 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-37-png.webp 368w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-37-300x149.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"bulkassigncategories\">Bulk Assign Categories to a Single Metric, Report or Dashboard</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>DataTools Pro allows you to bulk select Metrics, Dashboards and Reports so you can bulk update categories and status. To complete this task:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Select the first record in your desired bulk selection</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f3f7f6\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"801\" height=\"415\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-38-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10380 not-transparent\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f3f7f6; width:414px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-38-png.webp 801w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-38-300x155.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-38-768x398.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>2. <strong>Bulk select additional records 1 by 1:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hold the <strong>Ctrl </strong> button on your keyboard and click on the individual records that you would like to bulk edit<br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"ebf5f2\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #ebf5f2;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-39-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10381 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-39-png.webp 800w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-39-300x182.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-39-768x466.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>2. <strong>Bulk select records in sequence from first selected</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hold the <strong>Shift </strong>button on your keyboard and click the last record in sequence that you would like to select. DataTools will auto-select all records in between. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"e8f4f1\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #e8f4f1;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"812\" height=\"495\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-40-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10382 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-40-png.webp 812w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-40-300x183.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-40-768x468.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 812px) 100vw, 812px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Click on the &#8220;Edit X Metrics&#8221; button</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Select the category (Line of Business or Topic)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"e4e7e7\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #e4e7e7;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"834\" height=\"270\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-41-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10383 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-41-png.webp 834w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-41-300x97.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-41-768x249.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 834px) 100vw, 834px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Select 1 or multiple categories.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>6. Press &#8220;Assign&#8221; to bulk assign the categories.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>7. Close the window by clicking the close icon or click outside of the popup window.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-permissions-team-and-enterprise-versions\">Permissions (Team and Enterprise Versions)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We provide controls to restrict who can implement and modify tags within DataTools Pro. <br><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/manage-datatools-pro-account-and-users/\" title=\"\">Learn how to manage users and permissions </a></p>\n"
}